  <h2>Get started quickly</h2>
  <p class="lead">This is a starting point for creating mapping applications that combine the components and style from <a href="https://nycplanning.github.io/labs-ui/">Labs UI</a>, models and components from <a href="https://nycplanning.github.io/ember-mapbox-composer/">Ember Mapbox Composer</a>, and data from <a href="https://github.com/NYCPlanning/labs-layers-api">Labs Layers API</a>.</p>
  <p>Just fork this repository and get started.</p>

  <p> <strong>></strong> This app incorporates features that we reuse in many of our apps. Components include:</p>

  <p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>bbl-lookup</strong> for searching BBLs</li>
      <li><strong>tooltip-renderer</strong> for showing tooltips on the map</li>
      <li><strong>icon-tooltip</strong><sup class="float-right">{{icon-tooltip tip='This is the tooltip' class="dark-gray"}}</sup> for showing tooltips outside of the map</li>
      <li><strong>lookup-layer-group</strong> for adding layer-group legend items</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

<p>
    <strong>></strong> Labs <a href="https://github.com/NYCPlanning/labs-search-api">Search API</a> provides a search container for users to search addresses (geosearch) or layer-groups. Comments are added in the code to indicate where to edit when making layer-groups searchable, just search "layer-group search" to find these comments.
